#
# Category-partition test specification for NumberRangeRule.validate
# Passay project — section 3.1.4 (TSLGenerator)
#
# Configuration under test:
#   NumberRangeRule(10, 20, matchBehavior, reportAllFailures)
#   Forbidden integers: 10 .. 19 (lower inclusive, upper exclusive)
#
# Generate test frames:
#   TSLGenerator NumberRangeRule.tsl   (or: tslgenerator NumberRangeRule.tsl)
# Expected: 51 test frames (TF-1 .. TF-51)
#
# JUnit sample: NumberRangeRuleCategoryPartitionTest.java (15 representative frames)
#

Parameters:
Forbidden number in password:
  no digit from 10..19. [property NoHit]
  digit 9 below range. [property Below]
  digit 20 at or above upper bound. [property Above]
  digit 10 in range. [property In10]
  digit 15 in range. [property In15]
  digit 19 in range. [property In19]
  digits 12 and 17 both in range. [property Multi]

Digit position in password:
  number at start.
  number in middle.
  number at end.

Match behavior:
  contains
  starts with
  ends with

Failure reporting:
  report all matching numbers. [property RptAll]
  report first matching number only. [property RptFirst]

# EndsWith only applies when testing in-range single digits 10, 15, 19
ends with. [if In10 or In15 or In19]

# reportAll vs reportFirst: only meaningful when two in-range digits appear
report first matching number only. [if Multi]
report all matching numbers. [if !Multi]
